        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 1:38PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 138 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sylvester, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merkel, Trent, Neinda, Sylvester, Noodle, Longworth, Mccaulley, and
The Intersection Of Us-180 And Ranch Road 126.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 259 and 269.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
